          • [ - ] bagsbags - member since 26-Nov-15

            @Ouftey there's big difference between past chelsea with current juve. First, Most of juve attack is built from back. Buffon throw the ball to defender and then start to built attack with combination of short, long, cross, one two. Second The way juve defend its not park the bus as chelsea did. Juve didn't sat deep in their defence. If you see juve, Juve defense line was always in the middle between penalty box with halfway line. the defense is started from attacker chasing the ball, and midfielder pressurizing Man City players by closing down opponents using one/two players. Park the bus means that you'll put almost whole team sitting deep inside their defense. The defense line will be closer to GK. And midfield line will be closer to defense line. So no space allowed between defense & midfield. one striker left alone for counter attack. Park the bus will let opponents to built attacks invite them to come inside while they wait deep inside to do quick sudden counter attacks.
